findings.suggested_fix:
Replace the bare `>/dev/null 2>&1 || true` pattern with a pattern that captures stderr and logs a warning on non-zero exit while still returning 0:
```bash
prune_docker_caches() {
  docker builder prune -f --keep-storage "${BUILD_CACHE_KEEP:-5GB}" \
    >/dev/null 2>/tmp/_prune_err || \
    { echo "[autodeploy] WARN: builder prune failed: $(cat /tmp/_prune_err)" >&2; }
  docker image prune -f >/dev/null 2>/tmp/_prune_err || \
    { echo "[autodeploy] WARN: image prune failed: $(cat /tmp/_prune_err)" >&2; }
  rm -f /tmp/_prune_err
  return 0
}
```
This keeps the function best-effort (always returns 0) while surfacing failures to the log that autodeploy already writes.
